I didn’t want to do this, but the second I heard someone say, “poor Casey Anthony”, something snapped inside of my soul, and then it died… and then it came back to life like an angry demon vampire, a demon vampire that’s hungry. Anyone who thinks Casey is the victim in any universe clearly doesn’t know this case, so I’ve got to give a good old fashioned refresher.
True crime milk. Yum, yum, yum!
Have you seen today’s video yet? Watching Episode 2 now, and it gets so much worse.
Why are we paying for the news though? Especially when all of these sites have a million ads? You know they getting paid!!
Show of hands. Who thinks that tear she was trying to push out ever fully formed and made its great escape off of her lying face?
I wouldn’t wish this hell on… the people who think I’m guilty!! 🙄🙄🙄🤦🏻‍♀️🤦🏻‍♀️🤦🏻‍♀️ Ok, Casey
Voldemort’s real name wasn’t Tom Riddle… it was Casey Anthony 😨
Crazy how two people can listen to the exact same thing yet HEAR something completely different @crimeweeklypod @derricklevasseur
Did the knife have to be that big, though?

A lot of people ask me about my brow girl, and they say I can’t possibly have as much fun as I make it seem when going to get my brows tinted and waxed, but I do. If you’re in the Rochester area and you want the most banging brows on the block, go see her. She did not pay me for this, I’m not getting free services in return- Amanda has been doing my brows for decades, she’s one of the hardest working women I know and if you’re a client of hers, she’ll bend over backwards for you. @amanda_esthetics ❤️❤️❤️
Not only is she adorable, but I think we can all relate to her this month. I can’t wait for January to leave and hide its face in shame for what its put us through!
Knowing what we now know… do we allow Dale Cooper to remain in the booth?

You guys are beyond awesome 🥹🥹🥹 I’m really so moved and so thankful that together we can do a little good in this world to battle the evil, we can throw out a little light to illuminate the dark. I’m kind of emotional about it now, and as many of you know, “emotional” Is not a state of comfort for me, but I know that none of my words can express the comfort that this community gives me, or the gratitude and pride I feel when I see us all come together for something real, something important. RIP Amore, we got you ❤️❤️❤️
Sorry, I’m done gushing after this. But trust when I say this made my day, my MONTH… and I’m going to be walking around smiling like a damn fool for the rest of the night 🥹❤️

I miss vacation Stephanie. She seemed cool and happy. All jokes aside, I’ve been so busy these past few months I never got a chance to share most of these pics or give a huge shout out to the awesome people at @sandalsemeraldbay for always bending over backwards to give us the best experience when we were there last September. Every single person we encountered was so kind, so friendly and welcoming and I would not hesitate to go back as often as humanly possible. If you’re looking for an amazing vacation, go there now. Drop everything, it can wait. You haven’t lived until you’ve slid into the crystal clear waters of the Caribbean. And if anyone wants to know any fun facts about Exuma, the island we were on, or the Bahamas in general, you know I did my research and I got all the details, from pirates to swimming pigs @adam_geee_

“Childhood should be carefree, playing in the sun; not living a nightmare in the darkness of the” soul” David Pelzer: A Child Called “It”
You all know that crimes against children have a strong grasp on my heart, and there’s a special place in hell for any person who would take part in snuffing out the light of an innocent childhood. I don’t always get to feel positive or good about these cases, usually I feel pretty bad about them for a long time. I’m so glad that we were able to do something for Amore. I only wish she were here, because that baby girl knew no love in the final days of her life, and seeing all of you come together to show her love and to help her mom… I think that would have given her the biggest smile. Thank you again. ❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️
Days like this, I love my job 🍷 ❤️

Are you a fan of Harloween? Are you a fan of horror movies? Do you get a delicious thrill of terror when something goes bump in the night? I know I’ve been teasing you all with little clips and hints about this project I’ve been involved in, but I am finally able to unveil the poster for this film titled The Offering. Keep an eye out for a Q&A with the creators of this film @colemanbrosfilms 🎬 Artwork by @deaditecorpse
Been a rough month. I made this one for me 🤣 And why did I get so excited when I jumped into the ocean? The real ones know… 😉

First, a new video should be posting today or tomorrow, depending on the mercurial YouTube Gods 🤞 Also,  have you seen the full interview with @colemanbrosfilms on their YouTube channel? It’s officially March, that means The Offering will be available to view on YT this month, so make sure you’re subscribed to James and Vince so you don’t miss it! There’s something for everyone! If you’re pro-Stephanie, you can support me, if you’re anti-Stephanie, you can make fun of me on Reddit and talk about how stupid my face looks (let’s be honest, you’re still a fan) Its a win/win! New video up now! 28 year old Hong Kong influencer Abby Choi was last seen alive on February 21st, 2023. No one could have predicted the reality of what happened to her. Abby left behind 4 young children and countless friends and loved ones. The motive for taking her life is completely senseless.

The last time I “went out” on St Patricks Day, I was the nightclub manager at a little club called ONE in downtown Rochester. I was able to party and work at the same time. Should we break the dry spell this year and at least have one too many Irish coffees? 🫠 What does everyone do on St Pattys?

If you’ve been following the journey of our short film, The Offering, you’ll be very excited to know that it will FINALLY be available to watch on March, 31st! I’m so excited to finally see all the hard work  that so many have put into this project come to life, and I’m so proud of James and Vince for pulling this off in a way I truly believe only they can. We hope to see this short transform into a full feature very soon! If you want to watch, make sure you are subscribed to @colemanbrosfilms on IG and YT, and I’ll make sure to keep reminding you as we get closer to the date. A girl really couldn’t ask for a better, more supportive group of friends then you all, and I’m feeling especially blessed to be able to share this with you ❤️❤️❤️
March 31st- save the date, get your mind blown @colemanbrosfilms

Happy birthday to my father, who shares the same birthday as another infamous outlaw, Clyde Barrow, and trust me, that checks out 🤣 Fathers are so important in the lives of little girls, and big girls, too, and I was lucky to have one who taught me to never settle for less than I deserved, to not give af what anyone else thought of me, and to ultimately respect myself ❤️ My mother showed me how to love and nurture, my father showed me how to take what I want from this world 💪🏻 and those two dichotomies made me who I am today. Happy birthday, Papa ❤️❤️

I’m so grateful to have a partner like @derricklevasseur because we can truly behave as equals with each other, we respect each other while also engaging in productive discussions and discourse. This time of year always makes me think of the many many years I spent, slinging cell phones at festivals and state fairs from morning till night. Surviving off of fried dough and beef jerky, holding my pee far beyond a healthy point because I refused to use a port a potty, needing to exhibit far more energy and social skills than my shriveled emotional brain could handle… but there were some really great times hidden amongst the sweat, dirt and perpetually sticky everything 🤣 And if you’re in one of these pics, you know exactly what I mean 👀❤️ Heres to remembering the past fondly, but feeling glad it’s the past 😉

New Crime Weekly News is out on audio! We're talking about something very time sensitive this week. Tomorrow, Dec. 28, the King Road house where 4 University of Idaho students were murdered is set to be demolished. Many people, including those closest to the victims, are worried that important evidence could be lost. 

Sign the petition against the demolition here: https://www.change.org/p/halt-the-demolition-of-king-road-house-until-after-trial
